  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "cp/mOdbdJAb5cznMlvJsfRQRwkM=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Powerhouse uses GraphQL SDL as the specification language for document models. This serves two purposes:\n\n- **State schema**: `type` definitions describe the document's data structure (e.g., `type TodoListState { items: [TodoItem!]! }`).\n- **Operations schema**: `input` definitions describe the payload for each operation (e.g., `input AddTodoItemInput { text: String! }`).\n\nGraphQL SDL was chosen because it provides a clear, structured schema that supports custom scalar types (like `OID`, `Currency`, `DateTime`), enforces non-null constraints, and serves as a machine-readable specification that both humans and AI agents can understand. This is the foundation of Powerhouse's \"Specification Driven Design & Development\" approach.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
